    "plan_content": "The plan is written and ready. Here's a summary of what I've designed:\n\n---\n\n## Plan Summary: Stepper Compound Component\n\n**4 changes total — 2 new files, 2 registry appends**\n\n### Architecture\n\nThe component follows the **`carousel.tsx` pattern** — two React contexts, custom hooks, function declarations, `data-slot` on every element, `cn()` for class merging:\n\n- **`StepperContext`** (root): shares `activeStep` + `orientation`\n- **`StepperItemContext`** (per-item): shares `step` + computed `state` (\"completed\" | \"active\" | \"pending\")\n\n### Files\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `ui/stepper.tsx` | **Create** — 7 exports: `Stepper`, `StepperItem`, `StepperTrigger`, `StepperTitle`, `StepperDescription`, `StepperSeparator`, `StepperContent` |\n| `examples/stepper-demo.tsx` | **Create** — 3-step horizontal stepper with `useState` + Prev/Next buttons |\n| `ui/_registry.ts` | **Append** `stepper` entry (no deps — pure React) |\n| `examples/_registry.ts` | **Append** `stepper-demo` entry with `registryDependencies: [\"stepper\", \"button\"]` |\n\n### Key Design Decisions\n\n- **`StepperSeparator` lives inside `StepperItem`** — the only way to give it state awareness without a `step` prop; the spec says \"each step has a StepperSeparator\" which confirms this placement\n- **Stepper root layout mirrors Tabs**: `flex-col` for horizontal orientation (indicators row on top, content below), `flex-row` for vertical\n- **No `cva`** — state is driven by `data-[state=...]` Tailwind modifiers on the elements themselves\n- **No third-party dependencies** — pure React + Tailwind\n\nThe full plan with complete file contents is at `/Users/timpietrusky/.claude/plans/floofy-whistling-tide.md`. Ready to implement when you approve!",
